AN ACT relating to animals; directing the Joint Interim Standing
Committee on Natural Resources to conduct a study
during the 2025-2026 interim concerning the sale of cats
and dogs by retail pet stores in this State; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law creates the Joint Interim Standing Committee on Natural
2 Resources. (NRS 218E.320) Existing law authorizes the Committee to: (1) evaluate
3 and review issues related to natural resources in this State; (2) conduct
4 investigations and hold hearings; and (3) conduct studies as directed by the
5 Legislature or Legislative Commission. Existing law requires the Committee to
6 make certain reports to the Legislature. (NRS 218E.330) This bill directs the
7 Committee to conduct a study during the 2025-2026 interim concerning the sale of
8 cats and dogs by retail pet stores in this State.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. The Joint Interim Standing Committee on
2 Natural Resources shall conduct a study during the 2025-2026
3 interim concerning the sale of cats and dogs by retail pet stores in
4 this State.
