1 2. The study must include, without limitation, an examination
2 of:
3 (a) The acquisition of cats and dogs by retail pet stores for resale
4 in this State; and
5 (b) The treatment of cats and dogs by retail pet stores after the
6 cats and dogs are acquired and before the cats and dogs are sold by
7 the retail pet stores.
8 3. The Committee shall include its findings relating to the
9 study in the report required by subsection 4 of NRS 218E.330 to be
10 prepared and submitted to the Director of the Legislative Counsel
11 Bureau for transmittal to the 84th Session of the Legislature.
